<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This section is characterised by urediniospores having few scattered germ pores and an echinulate wall without smooth areas. It is similar to section 
<taxonomicName class="Globothalamea" family="Discorbinellidae" genus="Milesina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="Milesina" order="Rotaliida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="section" section="Milesina">Milesina</taxonomicName>
in having an echinulate cell wall, but the number of germ pores is lower (only 5-7). The ITS sequences of the two sections are separated by a large genetic distance. So far, this section is represented only by the type species. Possibly, the North American 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. polystichi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="polystichi">M. polystichi</taxonomicName>
belongs to this section as well (see commentary to 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. whitei" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="whitei">M. whitei</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
